  "logical_conclusion": "No nontrivial continuous cardinal score can be both stable under arbitrary addition of alternatives and invariant under all positive affine q reparameterizations. Raw q differences retain cardinal and extension-stable information but require a q scale or free lambda. Local z-score and MAD remove that scale but make pairwise odds context-dependent. Rank gives up cardinality, while global normalization gives up locality. The present RZS symmetries therefore do not select a unique score; an additional operational convention or law is required.",
